Toss together romaine, Boston, iceberg lettuces and watercress in a large salad bowl. Halve, pit and peel the avocados and cut them into 1/2-inch pieces. Arrange chicken, bacon, tomato and avocado decoratively over the greens. Garnish the salad with the chopped egg and chives. Dressing Directions: Whisk together vinegar, mustard, salt and pepper to taste. Add CRISCO(R) oil in a slow stream, continuously whisking. Whisk dressing until thick and blended. Stir in Roquefort. Whisk dressing again and pour it over the salad. Toss salad well before serving.